eased","1267–1350":"1267–1350","1267–Female":"1267–Deceased","9 January 1338":"9 January 1338","Abt 1326":"about 1326","1341":"1341","1350":"1350","1292":"1292","1338":"1338","1326":"1326","1325":"1325","1302":"1302","1357":"1357","1267":"1267","1300":"1300","1365":"1365","1298":"1298","Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom","Dundee, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dundee, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Skottland":"Dundee, Scotland, United Kingdom","Kirkton on Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ramsay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish and English: variant (the usual spelling in Scotland) of   Ramsey  . The Scottish Ramsays derive from Simund <i>de Ramesie</i>, recorded before 1175, who went to Scotland from Ramsey (Huntingdonshire)."],"variants":[{"name":"Ramsey","meanings":["Scottish, English, and Irish (Antrim): habitational name from Ramsey (Huntingdonshire, now part of Cambridgeshire), from Old English <i>hramsa</i> ‘wild garlic’ + <i>ēg</i> ‘island, low-lying land’. Alternatively, the name may also arise from Ramsey (Essex), probably from the same etymology as the Huntingdonshire placename. However, this is unlikely to be the source of the Scottish surname. This form of the surname is also common in Ireland, where it is probably in most if not all cases an altered form of Scottish   Ramsay  ."]}]},{"name":"Malcolm","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of the medieval Gaelic name <i>Mael Coluim</i> ‘devotee of St Columba’. Columba was a 6th-century monk of Irish origin who played a leading part in the conversion to Christianity of Scotland and northern England;  see also  Callum   and   Colm .  He has always been one of the most popular saints in Scotland, but in the Middle Ages it was felt to be presumptuous to give the names of saints directly to children; instead their blessing was invoked by prefixing the name with <i>mael</i> ‘devotee of’ or <i>gille</i> ‘servant of’. Since the 1930s the given name has been used widely in the English-speaking world, not just by those with Scottish connections."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Malcolm Ramsay was born in 1298, in Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland, his father, Robert Ramsay - First Laird of Auchterhouse, was 31 and his mother, Lady Ramsay, was 32. He had at least 2 sons with Ella House. He died in 1365, in Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom, at the age of 67."},"et":{"1298–1365":"1298–1365","1292–1357":"1292–1357","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1302–1338":"1302–1338","1325–1365":"1325–1365","1326–Male":"1326–Surnud","1267–1350":"1267–1350","1267–Female":"1267–Surnud","9 January 1338":"9. jaanuar 1338","Abt 1326":"umbes 1326","1341":"1341","1350":"1350","1292":"1292","1338":"1338","1326":"1326","1325":"1325","1302":"1302","1357":"1357","1267":"1267","1300":"1300","1365":"1365","1298":"1298","Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Auchterhouse, Angus, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dundee, Angus, Scotland, United Kingdom":"Dundee, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland":"Auchterhouse, Forfarshire, Scotland","Auchterhouse, Dundee, Angus, Skottland":"Dundee, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Kirkton on Auchterhouse, Angus, Scotland":"Forfarshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1298–1365":"1298–1365","1292–1357":"1292–1357","1300–1341":"1300–1341","1302–1338":"1302–1338","1325–1365":"1325–1365","1326–Male":"1326–Kuollut","1267–1350":"1267–1350","1267–Female":"1267–Kuollut","9 January 1338":"9. tammikuuta 1338","Abt 1326":"noin 1326","1341":"1341","1350":"1350","1292":"1292","1338":"1338","1326":"1326